# Agent Instructions

This repository contains instruction files for AI-assisted code review and development.

## Instruction Files

**coding-instructions.md**
- Commit message format and philosophy
- General coding style and patterns
- Work patterns (bug fixes, features, cleanup)
- Whitespace rules and TODO/FIXME requirements

**review-instructions.md**
- Automated review request feedback process
- Four main capabilities: summary, analysis, interactive feedback, learning
- Integration with ReviewBoard MCP server
- Best practices for automated analysis and human oversight

**review-specifics.md**
- Template for repository-specific configuration
- Customize for each codebase under review
- Covers: naming conventions, architecture, current priorities, common issues

**agent-tooling-instructions.md**
- Agent-specific tooling mechanics and usage guidelines
- How agents should interact with development tools
- Tool-specific flags and options for automated workflows
- Separate from coding style - focuses on tool execution

## Usage

- For normal coding tasks, reference **coding-instructions.md** and **agent-tooling-instructions.md**
- When performing code reviews or analyzing commits, reference **coding-instructions.md**, **review-instructions.md**, and **review-specifics.md**
- For tool usage mechanics (debuggers, build systems, etc.), reference **agent-tooling-instructions.md**
